The paper [BIB/Boege_86a] contains a discussion of heuristics for Groebner basis computations and variable orderings on several examples.
It discusses the following examples:
Hairer_1 as Hairer 1 Hairer_2 as Hairer 2 Hairer_2_1 as Hairer 2 Katsura_3 as Katsura Katsura_4 as Katsura Katsura_5 as Katsura Gerdt-85 as Gerdt Gonnet-83 as Gonnet Butcher as Butcher Raksanyi as Raksanyi Rose as Rose Trinks as Trinks Trinks_1 as Small Trinks
